					<head>Liturgy</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n80040114" rend="visible">
						<summary>A festival prayer book for Rosh ha-Shanah and Yom Kipur, according to the Franco-German rite.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n80040114">
							<locus from="1r" to="165v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Maḥzor</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מחזור</title>
							<note>
								<p>The volume contains a numer of notes in Italian cursive script in the margin. Apparently, it is an Ashkenazi rite used by Ashkenazi congregations in Italy.</p>
								<p>See further <ref target="Davidson_1924"/>.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1v" to="26v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for the first day of Rosh ha-Shanah</title>
							<filiation>Cf. the contents of Or 2733, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">665</ref>.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="26v" to="49v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for the second day of Rosh ha-Shanah</title>
							<filiation>Cf the contents of Or 2733, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">665</ref>.</filiation>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="49v" to="165v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Yom Kipur</title>
							<note>
								<p>Shaḥarit begins on folio 68v, musaf on folio 101r, minḥah on folio 136v, and ne῾ilah on folio 152v.</p>
								<p>A list of poetical pieces of Yom Kipur is given on folios 48v-49r.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment.</support>
								<extent>165 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>190</height>
										<width>170</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>140</height>
										<width>90</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>165 folios (+ 2 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 4 at the end. </p>
									<p>Parallel Hebrew foliation in Italian script up to folio 49r, and another from folio 49v to the end was added later.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 8 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires, cut away for the most part.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>2 leaves missing after folio 83 and another 2 after folio 87.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="23" writtenLines="22">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Initial words written in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Numerous marginal notes by various hands.</p>
									<p>The front margins have in some cases been cut away.</p>
									<p>Deleted paragraphs (erasure of censor?) e.g., folios 42v, 110r, 152r, 122r, 132r.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi square and semi-cursive script, partially punctuated, with a number of notes in Italian scripts.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
